### File Descriptions
```
app.py
- The main backend Python file implementing the web application using a web framework (e.g., Flask).
- Handles routing for all 10 pages, data loading from local text files, business logic, and interaction with the frontend.
- Manages reading and writing to the data files in the 'data' directory.
- Implements search, filter, playlist management, and statistics functionalities.

data/
- Directory containing all local text files storing the application's data as specified.
- Each file corresponds to a data entity: songs, artists, albums, genres, playlists, and playlist songs.

templates/
- Contains HTML template files for each of the 10 pages defined in the requirements.
- Each template includes the specified elements with their IDs for frontend rendering.
- Templates use templating syntax to dynamically display data passed from app.py.

static/
- Contains static assets used by the web application.
- css/styles.css: Stylesheet for consistent styling across pages.
- js/scripts.js: JavaScript for client-side interactivity (e.g., button actions, dynamic content updates).
- images/: Folder for storing cover art, artist photos, album covers, and other images referenced in the UI.

This structure keeps the backend logic consolidated in a single Python file for simplicity, while separating frontend templates and static assets for maintainability and clarity. It aligns with the project requirements and supports all specified features and pages.
